text: Explore our beautiful 11-acre wooded campus in Holly Springs. To schedule a tour or visit the school, please visit our Campus Tours page at https://www.montessoricenter.org/admissions/campus-tours/.

We welcome families from all backgrounds and offer an inclusive admissions process. New families can explore programs, schedule remote tours, and submit applications online through our Admissions page.

Our admissions process is transparent, welcoming, and supportive. Whether you're considering our school or ready to apply, we are here to help. Learn more about each step at https://www.montessoricenter.org/admissions/admissions-process/.

We offer multiple tuition payment plans and billing options to fit family needs. A complete tuition schedule and billing details regarding cost, prices, and fees are available at https://www.montessoricenter.org/admissions/tuition-fees/.
We offer need-based financial aid evaluated through ISM FAST. For application details and support, visit https://www.montessoricenter.org/admissions/financial-aid/.

Montessori education encourages independence, confidence, and creativity through hands-on learning, student-centered classrooms, and a differentiated curriculum. Learn more at https://www.montessoricenter.org/about/about-montessori/.

Our mission is to foster a lifelong joy of learning while nurturing each child’s unique strengths, interests, and goals. We prepare students for a 21st-century globalized world. Learn more at https://www.montessoricenter.org/about/school-philosophy/.

The New School Montessori Center is a private Montessori school in Holly Springs serving children from infancy through 8th grade. Learn more about our school at https://www.montessoricenter.org/about/.

Founded in the 1980s, The New School Montessori Center has its roots as a training center for Montessori educators. To learn more about our history, read about our journey at https://www.montessoricenter.org/about/history/.

Our FAQ covers many of your likely questions, including topics like comparisons with charter schools and other educational models, classroom structure, curriculum areas, and the daily Montessori routine. Browse FAQs at https://www.montessoricenter.org/about/faqs/.

Contact us or get in touch with the school at (919) 303-3636 or info@montessoricenter.org. Our campus is located at 5617 Sunset Lake Road, Holly Springs, NC 27540. You can also access our contact page to submit your questions via the website.
